 {"id":"asupersync-3qv04.5","title":"[WASM] React and Next framework adapters","description":"Implement the framework-facing adapter layers on top of the real browser package surfaces.

Important scope rule:
- direct runtime execution is a client-hydrated browser concern;
- Next.js server/node/edge paths are explicit bridge-only lanes by design, not full direct-runtime targets.

This track owns the React and Next user-facing adapters, lifecycle semantics, and bridge behavior necessary for real application consumption.","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":1200,"created_at":"2026-03-06T07:15:08.081026776Z","created_by":"CopperForest","updated_at":"2026-03-06T15:15:57.074266195Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["adapters","frameworks","next","react","wasm"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.5","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3qv04","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:15:08.081026776Z","created_by":"CopperForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.5","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3qv04.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:19:03.676578332Z","created_by":"CopperForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.5","depends_on_id":"asupersync-3qv04.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:19:03.720262400Z","created_by":"CopperForest","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":2398,"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.5","author":"CopperForest","text":"[2026-03-06 CopperForest] This track encodes an important product boundary: the goal is not full direct-runtime parity across every JS runtime. The intended direct execution lane is client-hydrated browser code. Next server/node/edge lanes are explicit bridge-only contexts by design. Future work should resist scope creep toward run-everything-everywhere and instead make the intended client + bridge model excellent, deterministic, and easy to consume.","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:15:34Z"},{"id":2406,"issue_id":"asupersync-3qv04.5","author":"CopperForest","text":"Boundary clarification for this whole track:

The goal is not to pretend the full runtime should execute directly in every JS environment. The documented target is: direct runtime execution only inside hydrated browser client boundaries. Node/server/edge integrations are still important, but they are bridge/adaptor surfaces and should remain explicit as such.

Keeping that distinction in the backlog prevents scope creep and avoids misleading future work into building unsupported "same runtime everywhere" packaging claims.","created_at":"2026-03-06T07:29:01Z"}]}
